Package expenditureprogram

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DisplaySpreadsheet
    This class displays a spreadsheet that can be modified by the user
    EditExpense
    This class allows the user to edit a specific expense in a separate JFrame and updates the original spreadsheet
    Expense
    This class creates an expense that specifies the name of the expense and how much is spent on this expense every month
    ExpenseLinkedList
    This class stores all ExpenseNodes in a custom linked list and allows the Spreadsheet class to modify the linked list based on user input
    ExpenseNode
    This class stores the nodes of the ExpenseLinkedList
    Login
    This class displays the login screen when the user launches the program
    Menu
    This class displays the main menu of the program once the user has logged in
    Register
    This class displays the register section of the program, used only when the user logs into the program without an account
    Run
    This class allows the user to launch and run the program
    Spreadsheet
    This class displays the expenses in a table, similar to a spreadsheet format
    SpreadsheetSelect
    This class displays a frame where the user can select previously stored spreadsheets of expenses
